WorkItem.Description:
I'm not sure if this is well-formed svg or not - but inkscape renders it ok.
 
With a fragment like this:
 
     <g transform="scale(0.75 0.75) translate(65 125)" >
     <svg viewBox="0 0 400 400" id="2" width="400px" height="400px">
     <g>
    <line x1="200" y1="120" x2="200" y2="280" style="fill:none;stroke:rgb(0,0,0);stroke-width:10"></line>
    </g>
    </svg>
 
The transform is not being applied. I tracked it down to the way the transform is being used in SvgFragment::Render. The stored transform is being put in a temporary variable (oldTransform) and replaced by a transform which , it seems, centres and zooms the viewbox. The snippet below shows what I did to get the transform from the fragment to be applied - but it the viewbox transform is now ignored. So it's obviously not a proper fix.
 
            // base.Render(graphics);      originally
 
            if (oldTransform != null)
            {
                graphics.Transform = oldTransform;
            }
 
            base.Render(graphics);  // transform parsed from file now works
